-- Shanghai's First-Half New Home Sales by Square Meter Slide 57%, Uwin Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-07T01:21:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/shanghai-s-first-half-new-home-sales-by-square-meter-slide-57-uwin-says.html

          
          
             Shanghai’s sales of new homes fell 57
percent in the first six months of the year on government
measures to cool the property market, Shanghai Uwin Real Estate
Information Services Co. said.  
 A total of 3.57 million square meters was sold in
Shanghai’s primary market for the period, compared with 8.24
million square meters a year earlier, Uwin said.  
